para.computeroutput: 'MD Initialized. Version d.d.d.d'
'MD Initialized. Version d.d.d.d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
Issued upon successful completion of task initialization.

para.computeroutput: 'SB Pipe Read Error, App will exit. Pipe Return Status = 0x%08X'
'SB Pipe Read Error, App will exit. Pipe Return Status = 0x%08X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event is issued following error return from CFE_SB_RcvMsg call.

para.computeroutput: 'Recovered Dwell Table #d is valid and has been copied to the MD App'
'Recovered Dwell Table #d is valid and has been copied to the MD App'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
Issued upon successful recovery of a Dwell Table.

para.computeroutput: 'MD App will reinitialize Dwell Table #d because recovered table is not valid'
'MD App will reinitialize Dwell Table #d because recovered table is not valid'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
Issued when a Dwell Table is recovered and found to be invalid.

para.computeroutput: 'Dwell Table(s) are too large to register: d > d bytes, d > d entries'
'Dwell Table(s) are too large to register: d > d bytes, d > d entries'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: CRITICAL
Cause:
Issued when a CFE_TBL_ERR_INVALID_SIZE error message is received from CFE_TBL_Register call. Load structure can be reduced by reducing MD_DWELL_TABLE_SIZE, number of entries per Dwell Table.

para.computeroutput: 'CFE_TBL_Register error 0x%08X received for tbl#d'
'CFE_TBL_Register error 0x%08X received for tbl#d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: CRITICAL
Cause:
Issued when an error message, other than CFE_TBL_ERR_INVALID_SIZE, is received from CFE_TBL_Register call.

para.computeroutput: 'Dwell Tables Recovered: d, Dwell Tables Initialized: d'
'Dwell Tables Recovered: d, Dwell Tables Initialized: d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
Issued at the end of Table Initialization, specifying how many tables were recovered and how many initialized.

para.computeroutput: 'No-op command, Version d.d.d.d'
'No-op command, Version d.d.d.d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
Issued upon receipt of a Memory Dwell no-op command.

para.computeroutput: 'Reset Counters Cmd Received'
'Reset Counters Cmd Received'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: DEBUG
Cause:
Issued upon receipt of a Memory Dwell Reset Counters command.

para.computeroutput: 'Start Dwell Table command processed successfully for table mask 0x%04X'
'Start Dwell Table command processed successfully for table mask 0x%04X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
Issued upon receipt of a Memory Dwell Start command. Upon receipt of this command, the specified tables are started for processing.

para.computeroutput: 'Stop Dwell Table command processed successfully for table mask 0x%04X'
'Stop Dwell Table command processed successfully for table mask 0x%04X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
Issued upon receipt of a Memory Dwell Start command. Upon receipt of this command, the specified tables are stopped.

para.computeroutput: 's command rejected because no tables were specified in table mask (0x%04X)'
's command rejected because no tables were specified in table mask (0x%04X)'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
None of the valid Table Ids (1..MD_NUM_DWELL_TABLES) are contained in the table mask argument for the Start Dwell or Stop Dwell command.

para.computeroutput: 'Msg with Invalid message ID Rcvd ID = 0x%04X'
'Msg with Invalid message ID Rcvd ID = 0x%04X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event is issued if the Memory Dwell task receives a message with an unrecognized Message ID.

para.computeroutput: 'Command Code d not found in MD_CmdHandlerTbl structure'
'Command Code d not found in MD_CmdHandlerTbl structure'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event is issued when a command for the Memory Dwell task is received with a function code which is not listed in the internal MD_CmdHandlerTbl structure, which is used to associate an expected length for the command.

para.computeroutput: 'Command Code d not found in command processing loop'
'Command Code d not found in command processing loop'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event is issued when a command for the Memory Dwell task is received with a function code which is not included in the task's command code processing loop.

para.computeroutput: 'Received unexpected error 0x%08X from CFE_TBL_GetStatus for tbl #d'
'Received unexpected error 0x%08X from CFE_TBL_GetStatus for tbl #d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event is issued on receipt of an unexpected error message from CFE_TBL_GetStatus. Normal processing continues; no special action is taken.

para.computeroutput: 'Cmd Msg with Bad length Rcvd: ID = 0x%04X, CC = d, Exp Len = d, Len = d'
'Cmd Msg with Bad length Rcvd: ID = 0x%04X, CC = d, Exp Len = d, Len = d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event is issued when the Memory Dwell task receives a command which has a length that is inconsistent with the expected length for its command code.

para.computeroutput: 'Msg with Bad length Rcvd: ID = 0x%04X, Exp Len = d, Len = d'
'Msg with Bad length Rcvd: ID = 0x%04X, Exp Len = d, Len = d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event is issued when the Memory Dwell task receives a message which has a length that is inconsistent with the expected length for its message id.

para.computeroutput: 'Successful Jam to Dwell Tbl#d Entry #d'
'Successful Jam to Dwell Tbl#d Entry #d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
This event is issued for a successful jam operation.

para.computeroutput: 'Successful Jam of a Null Dwell Entry to Dwell Tbl#d Entry #d'
'Successful Jam of a Null Dwell Entry to Dwell Tbl#d Entry #d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
This event is issued for a jam operation in which a null dwell entry is specified. A null entry is specified when the input dwell length is zero. All dwell fields (address, length, and delay) will be set to zero in this case.

para.computeroutput: 'Jam Cmd rejected due to invalid Tbl Id arg = d (Expect 1.. d)'
'Jam Cmd rejected due to invalid Tbl Id arg = d (Expect 1.. d)'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This error event is issued when a Jam Dwell Command is received with an invalid value for the table id argument. Values in the range 1..MD_NUM_DWELL_TABLES are expected.

para.computeroutput: 'Jam Cmd rejected due to invalid Entry Id arg = d (Expect 1.. d)'
'Jam Cmd rejected due to invalid Entry Id arg = d (Expect 1.. d)'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This error event is issued when a Jam Dwell Command is received with an invalid value for the entry id argument. Values in the range 1..MD_DWELL_TABLE_SIZE are expected.

para.computeroutput: 'Jam Cmd rejected due to invalid Field Length arg = d (Expect 0,1,2,or 4)'
'Jam Cmd rejected due to invalid Field Length arg = d (Expect 0,1,2,or 4)'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This error event is issued when a Jam Dwell Command is received with an invalid value for the field length argument.

para.computeroutput: 'Jam Cmd rejected because symbolic address 's' couldn't be resolved'
'Jam Cmd rejected because symbolic address 's' couldn't be resolved'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This error event is issued when symbolic address passed in Jam command couldn't be resolved by use of the on-board Symbol Table.

para.computeroutput: 'Jam Cmd rejected because address 0x%08X is not in a valid range'
'Jam Cmd rejected because address 0x%08X is not in a valid range'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
The resolved address (numerical value for symbol + offset) and field length specified by the Jam command were found to specify a dwell be outside valid ranges.

para.computeroutput: 'Jam Cmd rejected because address 0x%08X is not 32-bit aligned'
'Jam Cmd rejected because address 0x%08X is not 32-bit aligned'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
The Jam command specified a 4-byte read, and the resolved address (numerical value for symbol + offset) is not on a 4-byte boundary.

para.computeroutput: 'Jam Cmd rejected because address 0x%08X is not 16-bit aligned'
'Jam Cmd rejected because address 0x%08X is not 16-bit aligned'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
The Jam command specified a 2-byte read, and the resolved address (numerical value for symbol + offset) is not on a 2-byte boundary.

para.computeroutput: 'Didn't update MD tbl #d due to unexpected CFE_TBL_GetAddress return: 0x%08X'
'Didn't update MD tbl #d due to unexpected CFE_TBL_GetAddress return: 0x%08X'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This event is issued after the following sequence occurs: 1) CFE_TBL_GetStatus returned CFE_TBL_INFO_UPDATE_PENDING 2) CFE_TBL_Update returned CFE_SUCCESS, a call is made to 3) CFE_TBL_GetAddress returned something other than CFE_TBL_INFO_UPDATED.
When this happens, the newly loaded table contents are not copied to MD task structures.

para.computeroutput: 'Dwell Table is enabled but no processing will occur for table being loaded (rate is zero)'
'Dwell Table is enabled but no processing will occur for table being loaded (rate is zero)'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATIONAL
Cause:
1) The calculated rate, the total of delays for all active entries, equals zero, and 2) The table is enabled
If this load was initiated via ground command, the Table Id will be known from the command. If this load was recovered after a reset, a subsequent event message will identify the Table Id.

para.computeroutput: 'Dwell Table rejected because address (sym='s'/offset=0x%08X) in entry #d couldn't be resolved'
'Dwell Table rejected because address (sym='s'/offset=0x%08X) in entry #d couldn't be resolved'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
The specified symbol wasn't found in the system symbol table. This could be either because there is no symbol table, or because the symbol isn't present in an existing symbol table.
If this load was initiated via ground command, the Table Id will be known from the command. If this load was recovered after a reset, a subsequent event message will identify the Table Id.

para.computeroutput: 'Dwell Table rejected because address (sym='s'/offset=0x%08X) in entry #d was out of range'
'Dwell Table rejected because address (sym='s'/offset=0x%08X) in entry #d was out of range'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
The specified address was not in allowable memory ranges.
If this load was initiated via ground command, the Table Id will be known from the command. If this load was recovered after a reset, a subsequent event message will identify the Table Id.

para.computeroutput: 'Dwell Table rejected because length (d) in entry #d was invalid'
'Dwell Table rejected because length (d) in entry #d was invalid'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
The dwell table contains an invalid value for a dwell length.
If this load was initiated via ground command, the Table Id will be known from the command. If this load was recovered after a reset, a subsequent event message will identify the Table Id.

para.computeroutput: 'Dwell Table rejected because value of enable flag (d) is invalid'
'Dwell Table rejected because value of enable flag (d) is invalid'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
The dwell table's enable value was neither zero nor one.
If this load was initiated via ground command, the Table Id will be known from the command. If this load was recovered after a reset, a subsequent event message will identify the Table Id.

para.computeroutput: 'Dwell Table rejected because address (sym='s'/offset=0x08X) in entry #d is not properly aligned for a d-byte dwell'
'Dwell Table rejected because address (sym='s'/offset=0x08X) in entry #d is not properly aligned for a d-byte dwell'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
Either a 4-byte dwell was specified and address is not 4-byte aligned, or a 2-byte dwell was specified and address is not 2-byte aligned.
If this load was initiated via ground command, the Table Id will be known from the command. If this load was recovered after a reset, a subsequent event message will identify the Table Id.

para.computeroutput: 'Successfully set signature for Dwell Tbl#d to 's''
'Successfully set signature for Dwell Tbl#d to 's''

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
A 'Set Signature' command was received and processed nominally to associate a signature with the specified dwell table. All dwell packets derived from that dwell table will include the specified signature string.

para.computeroutput: 'Set Signature cmd rejected due to invalid Tbl Id arg = d (Expect 1.. d)'
'Set Signature cmd rejected due to invalid Tbl Id arg = d (Expect 1.. d)'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This error event is issued when a Set Signature Command is received with an invalid value for the table id argument. Values in the range 1..MD_NUM_DWELL_TABLES are expected.

para.computeroutput: 'Set Signature cmd rejected due to invalid Signature length'
'Set Signature cmd rejected due to invalid Signature length'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
This error event is issued when a Set Signature Command is received with a string not containing null termination within the allowable length.

para.computeroutput: 'Dwell Table rejected because Signature length was invalid'
'Dwell Table rejected because Signature length was invalid'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: ERROR
Cause:
The dwell table contains an invalid Signature (not null terminated).
If this load was initiated via ground command, the Table Id will be known from the command. If this load was recovered after a reset, a subsequent event message will identify the Table Id.

para.computeroutput: 'Dwell Table d is enabled with a delay of zero so no processing will occur'
'Dwell Table d is enabled with a delay of zero so no processing will occur'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATIONAL
Cause:
1) The calculated rate, the total of delays for all active entries, current equals zero 2) The table is currently enabled

If the command either changes the delay values in the table (such that the total delay is 0) while the table is enabled, or if the table is enabled while the total delay value is 0, this event will be sent.

para.computeroutput: 'MD Dwell Tbl verify results: good = %d, bad = %d, unused = %d'
'MD Dwell Tbl verify results: good = %d, bad = %d, unused = %d'

detaileddescription.para:
Type: INFORMATION
Cause:
This event message is issued when a table validation has been completed for memory dwell table load
The good field is number of entries that passed, the bad field is number of entries that failed, the unused field is the number of entries that weren't checked because they were marked unused.
